==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English boras, from Anglo-French boreis, from Medieval Latin borac-, borax, from Arabic būraq, from Pahlavi būrak, from Persian būrah

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|-}}

#A white or gray/grey [[crystalline]] salt, with a slight [[alkaline]] taste, used as a [[flux]], in [[solder]]ing metals, making [[enamel]]s, fixing colors/colours on [[porcelain]], and as a soap etc
#{{chemistry}} the [[sodium]] [[salt]] of [[boric acid]], Na<sub>2</sub>B<sub>4</sub>O<sub>7</sub>, either [[anhydrous]] or with 5 or 10 [[molecule]]s of [[water of crystallisation]]; [[sodium tetraborate]]

